=================================================================================================================================
						WORD SENSE DISAMBIGUATION
				A UNIFIED EVALUATION FRAMEWORK AND EMPIRICAL COMPARISON

				Alessandro Raganato, Jose Camacho-Collados and Roberto Navigli
=================================================================================================================================


This package contains four directories and the reference paper ("EACL17_WSD_EvaluationFramework.pdf"):


* Evaluation_Datasets: Evaluation datasets from the unified evaluation framework (more information in the README of the directory).

* Training_Corpora: Sense-annotated training corpora used in the evaluation framework by supervised systems (more information 
	            in the README of the directory).

* Output_Systems_ALL: Output of all the comparison systems included in the reference paper. Results for the concatenation of all
		      dataset ("ALL").

* Data-Validation: Guidelines and script to validate the conformity of sense-annotated datasets to the standard format.



=================================================================================================================================
REFERENCE PAPER
=================================================================================================================================

When using these resources, please refer to the following paper:

	Alessandro Raganato, Jose Camacho-Collados and Roberto Navigli. 
	Word Sense Disambiguation: A Unified Evaluation Framework and Empirical Comparison
	In Proceedings of European Chapter of the Association for Computational Linguistics (EACL), 
	Valencia, Spain, April 3-7, 2017. 

If you use any of the datasets, please also cite the corresponding reference paper of the task.

